    - target: {fileID: 3845059045047119735, guid: 5ba2e71648a4cb449be3dae70897a004, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Name
      value: DialogueCanvas
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 4204176042606351715, guid: 5ba2e71648a4cb449be3dae70897a004, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "It is late at night and I am thinking too hard; the racket smelled
        still of sweat and off brand griptape from the cornerstore by Kirkland. \n\nIt
        is in times like these, times I rummage a bit too hard through history, times
        I\u2019ve slouched too long in the mundane routine, times I am discontent
        with the in-creeping morning that something starts moving again. \n\nIt whispers
        something funny through the crack underneath the door and asks to be fed.
        I never thought I had the strength for this: to confront absolutely anything.\n
        \nBut in this terrible hour I think I want nothing more than to be seven
        again; so the door swings forth and in a fraction of a second I see your
        backside scampering. I never thought I had the strength for this: the chase
        and the re-openings. \n\nBut somehow I find myself scrambling, starving to
        catch you\u2014here we were behind closed doors, socking strangers a couple
        hours south side, past the thousand fainting lilacs brushing along their
        sweets, through the fresh break of dawn and splitting of an in-season peach.
        \n\nOh come on! Please stop moving so quickly! Can\u2019t you just sit here
        for a while? Just like we used to do? \n\nDancing your way into the jaws
        of another injury, sticking your hands into the dirt and then your nose before
        dozing off alongside the sun. \n\nDoors, through doors, through doors we
        run and I am so close to grabbing your wrist again.\n\nDoors and doors make
        their re-openings and I think I might be bed-bound by morning. \n\nCan you
        just please just stop running away?\n\nI have missed you more than I could
        remember and I just want to see your face. \n\nBut you turn the corner and
        I\u2019ve lost you again and I still, for the life of me, can\u2019t find
        a way to remember the last thing you said that day. \n\nI am nothing but
        you in sheep's clothing and you were nothing short of a shooting star. \n\nI
        love you. \n\nDo you hear me? \n\nI love you, so much so, I will spend my
        life opening these times trying to find you, again and again.\r\n"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
